-- Petrobras, Galp Call Onshore Sergipe Basin Discovery Commercially Viable
-- Joao Lima
-- 2010-04-27T09:04:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-27/petrobras-galp-call-onshore-sergipe-basin-discovery-commercially-viable.html

          
          
             Galp Energia SGPS SA, Portugal’s
biggest oil company, and Petroleo Brasileiro SA, Brazil’s state-
controlled oil producer, declared an onshore discovery in the
Sergipe Basin commercially viable, the Brazilian petroleum
regulator said.  
 The March 25 declaration about the Do-Re-Mi field in the
SEAL-T-412 block was posted on the National Petroleum Agency’s
Web site.  
          
          


  


        